google-genai (1.75.0-0ubuntu1~ppa1~noble2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Soften the pydantic runtime floor from `>= 2.9.0` to `>= 2.6` in
    both the pyproject patch and `debian/control`. The Avalan PPA's
    pydantic is capped at 2.6.4 by Noble's rustc 1.75 / maturin 1.3.2
    toolchain (which caps pydantic-core at 2.16.3); google-genai
    reaches only `BaseModel`, `ConfigDict`, `Field`, `PrivateAttr`,
    `model_validator`, `field_validator`, `ValidationError`,
    `TypeAdapter`, `SerializeAsAny`, and the `alias_generators`
    module ŌĆö all stable since pydantic 2.4. Without this softening,
    apt-get install of the Avalan chain failed with held-broken
    packages.
  * Ship a second quilt patch (drop-pep728-extra-items) that strips
    `extra_items=object` from the `DynamicAgentConfigParam` TypedDict
    declaration in `google/genai/_interactions/types/`. PEP 728 lands
    in Python 3.13 / typing-extensions 4.13; Noble ships 4.10, which
    raises `TypeError` at module import time with the keyword
    present. The keyword is purely a type-checker hint and has no
    runtime semantics, so dropping it leaves the runtime behaviour
    identical.

 -- Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>  Thu, 21 May 2026 18:00:00 -0300

google-genai (1.75.0-0ubuntu1~ppa1~noble1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial packaging of google-genai 1.75.0 for the Avalan PPA.
  * Runtime dep of Avalan's `vendors` extras. Not in Debian; the upstream
    sdist declares its license via the PEP 639 SPDX `license = "Apache-2.0"`
    string form Noble's python3-setuptools 68 rejects, and pins runtime
    floors on `google-auth >= 2.48.1`, `httpx >= 0.28.1`, and
    `typing-extensions >= 4.14.0` ŌĆö one (or several) patch releases above
    every matching package in Noble's archive.
  * Ship a quilt patch (pyproject-for-noble) that rewrites the SPDX
    license string to the legacy `license = { file = "LICENSE" }` table
    form Noble's setuptools accepts, drops the `twine`, `packaging`, and
    `pkginfo` entries from the build-system requires (those are
    distribution-upload helpers, not wheel builders), strips the
    Python 3.14 trove classifier unknown to Noble's setuptools, and
    softens the runtime floors to versions that resolve against Noble
    (4.10 for typing-extensions, 0.26 for httpx) and against the
    matching Avalan PPA build of google-auth (2.48.0 from sid; one
    patch release below upstream's nominal floor, with the gap living
    entirely in a typing fix the avalan path does not exercise).

 -- Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>  Wed, 20 May 2026 01:20:00 -0300
